---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Project Capsule | NearDivine Labs">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-24 pt-32">
    <section class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.15fr_0.85fr] lg:items-start">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-blue-300">Project Capsule</p>

        <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
          A desktop workspace for organizing project notes, decisions, files, and next actions.
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-base leading-8 text-zinc-400">
          Project Capsule is a Windows beta built for practical project tracking. It is designed to help capture active work, preserve useful context, and turn messy project progress into records that are easier to resume, review, or present later.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
          <a
            href="/downloads/project-capsule-beta.msi"
            download
            class="rounded-full bg-blue-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-400"
          >
            Download Windows Beta
          </a>

          <a
            href="/work"
            class="rounded-full border border-white/10 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-white/5"
          >
            View Projects
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-500">
          Windows MSI installer. Beta software; expect changes between versions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-400">
          Release details
        </h2>

        <dl class="mt-6 space-y-5">
          <div>
            <dt class="text-sm text-zinc-500">Status</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm font-medium text-white">Beta</dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="text-sm text-zinc-500">Platform</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm font-medium text-white">Windows</dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="text-sm text-zinc-500">Installer</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm font-medium text-white">MSI package</dd>
          </div>

          <div>
            <dt class="text-sm text-zinc-500">Primary use</dt>
            <dd class="mt-1 text-sm font-medium text-white">
              Project documentation and workflow capture
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20 border-t border-white/10 pt-12">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-blue-300">
          Workflow
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
          What Project Capsule is built to handle
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03]">
          <img
            src="/images/capsule/capsule-capture.png"
            alt="Project Capsule capture workspace screen"
            class="h-48 w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
              Capture work as it happens
            </h3>

            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">
              Keep notes, task context, and decisions in one place instead of scattering them across chats, loose files, and temporary scratch notes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03]">
          <img
            src="/images/capsule/capsule-context.png"
            alt="Project Capsule project context screen"
            class="h-48 w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
              Preserve project context
            </h3>

            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">
              Track what changed, what broke, what was tested, and what needs to happen next so projects are easier to resume later.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03]">
          <img
            src="/images/capsule/capsule-records.png"
            alt="Project Capsule documentation records screen"
            class="h-48 w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />

          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">
              Build reusable records
            </h3>

            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">
              Turn active build work into cleaner documentation, project summaries, case-study notes, and portfolio-ready records.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-8">
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr]">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
            Why it exists
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">
          <p>
            Hardware, software, automation, and robotics projects often create a documentation problem: the most useful context is produced while debugging, testing, and making tradeoffs, but that context is easy to lose.
          </p>

          <p>
            Project Capsule is being built to make that capture process more structured without turning it into a heavy project-management system.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-20 border-t border-white/10 pt-12">
      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-blue-300">
            Beta notes
          </p>

          <h2 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
            Current release scope
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">
          <p>
            The current beta is focused on the core desktop workflow: creating project records, capturing working notes, tracking next actions, and keeping enough project context in one place to reduce restart friction.
          </p>

          <p>
            Future versions may expand the release flow, documentation export options, project templates, and stronger support for portfolio or case-study generation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>